The paper proposes a model predictive control approach for manipulation tasks, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm also involves adapting to the accuracy requirements of a task, which involves decision-making and optimization (cs.AI). The use of an approximate online solution to the MDP and a trajectory optimizer with a deterministic model suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The manipulation task involves pushing objects, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a model predictive control approach suggests a focus on control theory (cs.SY).
